rComments: his lectures were very enjoyable, and he's very clear in the material. however, he's not so clear on what's on the tests; a LOT of memorizing (cladograms, class names). the tutorial are really pointless and the TA goes far too in depth on each class. the tests were based on material covered in lecture primarily so attending lecture is a must!

Awesome teacher, by far my favourite of my University career. He's great to listen to in lecture, he keeps you interested, and he makes very very fair tests. He is willing to sit down with you and figure out how you can study better, and does pop quizzes that are easy to boost marks for people that attend lecture.  Go to class you'll do well.
